records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which charges the following:
Count 1, fail to obey traffic officer/signal, contrary to Section 346.17(2t);
Count 2, negligent operation of a motor vehicle, contrary to Section 941.01(1);
Count 3, negligent operation of a motor vehicle, contrary to Section 941.01(1).
The State moves to amend the victim in count 3 of the Amended Information to Kevin Haese instead of Mark Henfer.  Court granted the motion.
GUILTY pleas entered to all three counts contained in the Amended Information.  Convicted.
On count 1, the defendant is sentenced to a total of six (6) months jail, under the Huber Law.  Two (2) months jail is imposed up front with a report date of 07-07-15 by 8:00 a.m.  The remaining four (4) months jail is stayed and will be imposed upon order of the court.  The Court authorizes transfer to either Sheboygan or Milwaukee County Jail and has no objection to electronic monitoring.
The defendant has credit for three (3) days.
$443.00 court costs imposed, to be paid by 08-03-15 or 9 days county jail for failure to pay.
On counts 2 and 3, sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling/combination;
2) Pay court costs;
3) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
4) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) defendant is to continue with his mental health treatment and take all medications as prescribed;
6) undergo any other counseling deemed appropriate by the agent.
Minutes.
